verses.text:
And I will lay it waste: it shall not be pruned, nor digged;
but there shall come up briers and thorns: I will also command the
clouds that they rain no rain upon it.

And the light of Israel shall be for a fire, and his Holy
One for a flame: and it shall burn and devour his thorns and his
briers in one day;

\add Their\add* bows also shall dash the young men to pieces;
and they shall have no pity on the fruit of the womb; their eye shall not
spare children.

They that see thee shall narrowly look upon thee, \add and\add*
consider thee, \add saying, Is\add* this the man that made the earth
to tremble, that did shake kingdoms;

And the \nd LORD\nd* said, Like as my servant Isaiah hath walked
naked and barefoot three years \add for\add* a sign and wonder upon
Egypt and upon Ethiopia;

And the key of the house of David will I lay upon his shoulder;
so he shall open, and none shall shut; and he shall shut, and none shall
open.

For he bringeth down them that dwell on high; the lofty city,
he layeth it low; he layeth it low, \add even\add* to the ground;
he bringeth it \add even\add* to the dust.

Yea, in the way of thy judgments, O \nd LORD\nd*, have we waited
for thee; the desire of \add our\add* soul \add is\add* to thy name,
and to the remembrance of thee.

For precept \add must be\add* upon precept, precept upon precept;
line upon line, line upon line; here a little, \add and\add* there a
little:\f + \fr 28.10  \ft must be: or, hath been\f*

Now therefore be ye not mockers, lest your bands be made strong:
for I have heard from the Lord \nd GOD\nd* of hosts a consumption,
even determined upon the whole earth.

That walk to go down into Egypt, and have not asked at my mouth;
to strengthen themselves in the strength of Pharaoh, and to trust
in the shadow of Egypt!

For thus saith the Lord \nd GOD\nd*, the Holy One of Israel;
In returning and rest shall ye be saved; in quietness and in confidence
shall be your strength: and ye would not.

As birds flying, so will the \nd LORD\nd* of hosts defend Jerusalem;
defending also he will deliver \add it; and\add* passing over he will
preserve it.

Lo, thou trustest in the staff of this broken reed, on Egypt;
whereon if a man lean, it will go into his hand, and pierce it: so
\add is\add* Pharaoh king of Egypt to all that trust in him.

Fear not, thou worm Jacob, \add and\add* ye men of Israel;
I will help thee, saith the \nd LORD\nd*, and thy redeemer, the Holy
One of Israel.\f + \fr 41.14  \ft men: or, few men\f*

I the \nd LORD\nd* have called thee in righteousness, and will
hold thine hand, and will keep thee, and give thee for a covenant
of the people, for a light of the Gentiles;

I will say to the north, Give up; and to the south, Keep not
back: bring my sons from far, and my daughters from the ends of the
earth;

Behold, I will do a new thing; now it shall spring forth;
shall ye not know it? I will even make a way in the wilderness, \add and\add*
rivers in the desert.

Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd* that made thee, and formed thee from the
womb, \add which\add* will help thee; Fear not, O Jacob, my servant;
and thou, Jesurun, whom I have chosen.

That frustrateth the tokens of the liars, and maketh diviners
mad; that turneth wise \add men\add* backward, and maketh their knowledge
foolish;

Bel boweth down, Nebo stoopeth, their idols were upon the beasts,
and upon the cattle: your carriages \add were\add* heavy loaden;
\add they are\add* a burden to the weary \add beast\add*.

Listen, O isles, unto me; and hearken, ye people, from far;
The \nd LORD\nd* hath called me from the womb; from the bowels of my
mother hath he made mention of my name.

And he hath made my mouth like a sharp sword; in the shadow
of his hand hath he hid me, and made me a polished shaft; in his
quiver hath he hid me;

Awake, awake, put on strength, O arm of the \nd LORD\nd*;
awake, as in the ancient days, in the generations of old. \add Art\add*
thou not it that hath cut Rahab, \add and\add* wounded the dragon?

He shall see of the travail of his soul, \add and\add* shall be
satisfied: by his knowledge shall my righteous servant justify many;
for he shall bear their iniquities.

Enlarge the place of thy tent, and let them stretch forth the
curtains of thine habitations: spare not, lengthen thy cords, and
strengthen thy stakes;

For thou shalt break forth on the right hand and on the left;
and thy seed shall inherit the Gentiles, and make the desolate cities
to be inhabited.

Fear not; for thou shalt not be ashamed: neither be thou confounded;
for thou shalt not be put to shame: for thou shalt forget the shame
of thy youth, and shalt not remember the reproach of thy widowhood any more.

For this \add is as\add* the waters of Noah unto me: for \add as\add*
I have sworn that the waters of Noah should no more go over the earth;
so have I sworn that I would not be wroth with thee, nor rebuke thee.

For the mountains shall depart, and the hills be removed;
but my kindness shall not depart from thee, neither shall the covenant
of my peace be removed, saith the \nd LORD\nd* that hath mercy on thee.

So shall my word be that goeth forth out of my mouth: it shall not
return unto me void, but it shall accomplish that which I please,
and it shall prosper \add in the thing\add* whereto I sent it.

For thus saith the \nd LORD\nd* unto the eunuchs that keep
my sabbaths, and choose \add the things\add* that please me, and take
hold of my covenant;

I create the fruit of the lips; Peace, peace to \add him that
is\add* far off, and to \add him that is\add* near, saith the \nd LORD\nd*;
and I will heal him.

For our transgressions are multiplied before thee, and our
sins testify against us: for our transgressions \add are\add* with us; and
\add as for\add* our iniquities, we know them;

The glory of Lebanon shall come unto thee, the fir tree, the pine
tree, and the box together, to beautify the place of my sanctuary;
and I will make the place of my feet glorious.

The Spirit of the Lord \nd GOD\nd* \add is\add* upon me; because the
\nd LORD\nd* hath anointed me to preach good tidings unto the meek;
he hath sent me to bind up the brokenhearted, to proclaim liberty
to the captives, and the opening of the prison to \add them that
are\add* bound;

I have spread out my hands all the day unto a rebellious people,
which walketh in a way \add that was\add* not good, after their own
thoughts;

A people that provoketh me to anger continually to my face;
that sacrificeth in gardens, and burneth incense upon altars of brick;\f + \fr 65.3 
\ft upon…: Heb. upon bricks\f*
